My meme

This meme is a look into the reality of being a university student and working as an intern.

meme

library(magick)
#cat 1
cat1 <- image_read("https://i.imgflip.com/ws6j3.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500)

#uni text
uni <- image_blank(width = 500, 
                   height = 500, 
                   color = "#F1F1F1") %>%
  image_annotate(text =  "YOU AS \nUNI GRADUATE", color = "#000000", size = 30, font = "Comic Sans MS", gravity = "center")

#cat 2
cat2 <- image_read("https://cdn.pixabay.com/photo/2019/12/05/02/42/cat-4674171__480.jpg") %>%
  image_scale(500)

#intern text
intern <- image_blank(width = 500, 
                      height = 500, 
                      color = "#F1F1F1") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "YOU AS \nINTERN", color = "#000000", size = 30, font = "Comic Sans MS", gravity = "center")

# making each row

cat_vector <- c(cat1, uni)
top_row <- image_append(cat_vector)
bottom_row <- image_append(c(cat2, intern))

# making the whole thing!
meme <- c(top_row, bottom_row) %>%
  image_append(stack = TRUE) %>%
  image_scale(800)

image_write(meme, "my_meme.png")

My animated GIF

I wanted to make a funny cat GIF where the cat hits you and says sorry, trying to win your heart back.

animatedGIF

library(magick)
# creating each frame
frame1 <- image_read("https://live.staticflickr.com/2257/2472284222_485fb85814_n.jpg") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "*punch*", size = 75, gravity = "center") %>%
  image_scale(500) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

frame2 <- image_read("https://pbs.twimg.com/media/EAmr-PAWsAEoiWR.jpg") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "I'm sorry", size = 100, gravity = "center") %>%
  image_scale(200) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

frame3 <- image_read("https://i.ytimg.com/vi/pr-f1MHqwBM/hqdefault.jpg?sqp=-oaymwEmCOADEOgC8quKqQMa8AEB-AGMBIAC4AOKAgwIABABGGUgUyhKMA8=&rs=AOn4CLAvEPFZ361zwl43fWTlmL8vulfesQ") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "come\nhere", size = 100, gravity = "center") %>%
  image_scale(350) %>%
  image_extent("500x500")

frame4 <- image_read("https://images.saymedia-content.com/.image/t_share/MTc0NjQwMTY2NTA0NDQxODQ2/cat-ladies-and-dudes-famous-women-and-men-in-history-and-the-love-of-cats.jpg") %>%
  image_annotate(text = "*smooch*", size = 100, gravity = "center") %>%
  image_scale(500)

# putting the frames in order using a vector
frames <- c(frame1, frame2, frame3, frame4)

# creating an animation
animation <- image_animate(frames, fps = 0.5)
image_write(animation, "my_animation.gif")
